        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <div type="transcription">
                    
<p rend="left">scoring many passages for future reflexion.—</p>
                    <p>My book on the Origin of species has been some time finished, &amp; will be published, as I hear from Murray, on Nov. 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.— I fear, if you ever read it, that the conclusions will be abominable 〈<hi rend="underline">several lines missing</hi>〉 &amp; I must stop, otherwise I shall be ruined.</p>
<p>My book in its present state is sadly too much condensed.—</p>
<p>Pray believe me | My dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Dated on the basis of CD’s remark that <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref> was to be published on 22 November 1859. This information was received in the preceding letter. According to Freeman 1977, p. 75, the publishers' trade sale was on 22 November and the book was published on 24 November.</note>
        </div>        
            
